title: FabrikatorMine
---d
Fabrikator: Yeah, man. That's a pretty tame one. Not bad for a beginner.
Fabrikator: Me, I've gotten old and I stay pretty busy here helping the scientists.
-> Yeah, I think I'll tackle that mine. I'd like to investigate the locations around here.
-> Hmm. I don't know...
Fabrikator: Well, in that case, why don't you borrow my old ultrabonded pickaxe.
Fabrikator: I don't use it, but it's light and indestructable. It's great for the ore down there.
-> And you just trust everyone who comes through here?
-> Yeah, thanks, I'll take you up on that! 
Fabrikator: Ok, man. Don't get yourself into too much danger. 
Fabrikator: Search and Rescue bot service gets expensive here on the periphery.
Fabrikator: Even more so further East of here into the mountains and plains due south.
<<if $hasPassedOut>>
Fabrikator: You've got a free bailout, though. Not a bad deal!
<<else>>
Fabrikator: You already used that bailout, man? I don't know if you're cut out for this.
<<endif>>
-> Ok, I appreciate your loaning me a pickaxe. Thank you.
Fabrikator: Take care...
<<jump End01>>
===

